Subclasses of GabotoException in org.oucs.gaboto.exceptions
 class EntityAlreadyExistsException
          Is thrown when an entity is added to the Gaboto model that already exists.
 class EntityClassNotFoundException
          Is thrown when the corresponding GabotoEntity class for an ontology type could not be determined.
 class EntityDoesNotExistException
          Is thrown when an GabotoEntity is accessed that does not exist in the model.
 class EntityPoolAmbiguousConfigurationException
          Is thrown if the GabotoEntityPoolConfiguration can be used for the creation of an GabotoEntityPool, but if it is ambiguous in some way.
 class EntityPoolInvalidConfigurationException
          Is thrown if an GabotoEntityPoolConfiguration is invalid.
 class ResourceDoesNotExistException
          Is thrown when an RDF resource is accessed that does not exist.
 class UnsupportedFormatException
          Is thrown if an unsupported format is supplied.
